    <element xsi:type="archimate:Capability" name="Technical Enablement" id="id-8aec125018cf467ea2681e70bb09664a"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Capability" name="Community Enablement" id="id-5798b21ce08a4f2dab4705ebb3c0cecd"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Capability" name="Enablement" id="id-a406a77811dc425490d7a3893fdf7f09"/>
  </folder>
  <folder name="Business" id="id-54c8d6a7d3434b159efb75fa0a850af8" type="business">
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Product" name="&lt;Product>" id="id-d34e3596dc6c4532babc52e840449983">
      <documentation>A product represents a coherent collection of services and/or passive structure elements, accompanied by a contract/set of agreements, which is offered as a whole to (internal or external) customers.</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Product>"/>
      <property key="Documentation (en)"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="&lt;Functionele dienst>" id="id-f56996d01fcb4e93b3c5bbf57ad3a0de">
      <documentation>An explicitly defined exposed business behavior.</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Functional Service>"/>
      <property key="Documentation (en)"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="&lt;Kader / Randvoorwaarde>" id="id-5fb7d30b1e7849828c69c9161c4838d6">
      <documentation>A contract represents a formal or informal specification of an agreement between a provider and a consumer that specifies the rights and obligations associated with a product and establishes functional and non-functional parameters for interaction.</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Constraint>"/>
      <property key="Documentation (en)"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Product" name="Marketplace" id="id-5629e90d1e1a41859191f0daa6b6f47f"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="Specifications for Acceptance in Marketplace" id="id-f0eeb328e0cf4943becde8bf1f841086"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Assesment of relevant technologies" id="id-e6e88837a19b4dcfbbe0b786e739aa97"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Product" name="Assesment framework for technologies" id="id-5c7ef81a10c34b61812ea50e5f72b4a7"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Deployment models" id="id-c8e4c5c39cdb4386a3e536d0f25443a5"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Digital readiness level assesment" id="id-bb5ff7ea9faa4c6688b831d98f998bef"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Digital readiness capacity building" id="id-4b5170a85f6e41fb8d9e6a8fe52b37fc"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Urban Insight &amp; XR Visualization" id="id-17a092d19c8d4d20afa8cccd3d1d101f">
      <documentation>Provides an immersive 2D/3D/XR interface for stakeholders to understand city data and proposal impacts</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Decision-Support Visualisation Service" id="id-9cad46d1a1a441d3bf7403b6a98e8e81">
      <documentation>The power of visualisation in a digital twin lies in its ability to transform data into understandable, interactive, and usable images that provide insight, detect problems, improve communication, and contribute to better decision-making and performance. Visualisation can be done in many ways: 2D (flat top view), 3D (to better visualise and analyse complex spatial data in a way that traditional 2D maps cannot). Glasses that project images overlapping with reality can also be used. Images can be static (current view of a situation) or very dynamic (interactive map where you can turn knobs to change indicators and immediately see the associated policy effects), contain many details and be realistic or not. The choice of visualisations depends on the nature of the data and the purpose of the digital twin. By combining different visualisation techniques, users can get a more complete picture of a system, understand processes, and make better decisions.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Spatio-Temporal Aware" id="id-101e16bde2cf43788a5a2f3513114da1">
      <documentation>The concept of time travel in a digital twin offers the possibility to study a situation in time. This concerns going back in time to give a reflection of how something was in the past. Digital Twins also make it possible to look ahead in time. This allows you to perform historical analyses, explore what-if scenarios, imagine or predict future situations.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Participatory Data Modification" id="id-cca459608fe44623b14d639ec8db230a">
      <documentation>A Digital Twin is interactive and dynamic (measured data from the environment – including measurements done by citizens, also known as Citizen Science, so that the citizen is involved in initiatives). The user of it will be able to do more than simply observe data and models. The user will be able to modify data.&#xD;
</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Policy Prediction &amp; Simulation" id="id-ec65df4e9a024a2284ecd3b8db7f7c9b">
      <documentation>Enables &quot;what-if&quot; analysis to forecast how decisions (e.g., closing a road) impact the city</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Urban Policy Layering" id="id-e6dcf14117924e86baeb77002520db31">
      <documentation>To visualise the physical living environment, data is layered on top of each other in a graphical environment. The data from the layers come from various registers and often represent policy choices or legal standards, and the sliders are the different policy ambitions in relation to the standards for, for example, noise or public green spaces. The layers can be controlled with sliders, so that interests can be balanced and fairly proportional to each other.&#xD;
</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Federated Data Sovereignty Service" id="id-5dbabaccf08a47e8886dd69ab3718655">
      <documentation>Governs the secure exchange of data across borders and sectors using machine-readable contracts</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Zero Trust Governance &amp; Security" id="id-964b0e9a1dfe4026a138978127fca0e7">
      <documentation>Centralises identity verification to ensure secure, sovereign access across all digital twin assets /&#xD;
&#xD;
Identification is a foundation of modern software systems that ensure efficient and secure functioning within digital infrastructures. These are supporting components that can provide access control and access rights, thereby preventing unsecured access. Identification also makes it possible to personalize systems for individual users or groups, so that the user interface or tailored content can be offered and that preferences and settings can be stored.&#xD;
</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Immersive Urban Experimentation Service" id="id-b8c2bbd6558b42afbc0a8f1620b5b5fd">
      <documentation>A great strength of a Digital Twin is the experience aspect. These experiences go beyond simply observing data and models; they enable people to virtually experiment, learn, and understand how something looks or functions. This is achieved by users interacting with a virtual copy. The interaction can take place in different ways. User-friendliness and an intuitive interface that makes it easy for users to navigate and perform the necessary actions are also important.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Privacy-Preserving Synthetic Data" id="id-2998b289141c49c9ac3203d2a83a9b42">
      <documentation>Generates high-quality simulated data for testing scenarios without exposing sensitive real-world behavior</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Real-time Urban Context Awareness" id="id-ad120f61af6b481a81ffa92e4e642e49">
      <documentation>Serves as the &quot;single source of truth&quot; by centralising and standardising data from sensors and databases</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Strategic KPI &amp; Maturity Monitoring" id="id-f538c14d2e3e4c50a1dbf21e8f3086e6">
      <documentation>Acts as the city's &quot;scoreboard&quot; to track progress against goals like the UN SDGs or U4SSC KPIs</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Contextual Indicator Discovery" id="id-83184051f17f42d0a64ffbed53d61654">
      <documentation>In a Digital Twin, various types of data are brought together to create as accurate a representation as possible of the policy choices. Digital Twins must speak the language and use images that policy makers recognize – including normalizing and standardizing the indicators used. A Digital Twin also provides contextual information that helps users understand what the data represents, where it comes from, how it was collected and how it should be interpreted. This is especially important because Digital Twins often contain complex and diverse data sources. It is essential for the successful use of Digital Twins in various domains.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Urban Intelligence &amp; ML Inference" id="id-e7a68c2a53c84175820f53c01e6bccfd">
      <documentation>Supports the development and deployment of advanced algorithms to improve urban predictions</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Citizen Co-creation &amp; Engagement" id="id-94c08516127647c9aa8095aedfac27a7">
      <documentation>Transforms the digital twin into a collaborative platform for public feedback and consensus building</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Opportunity-Finding Simulation Service" id="id-2c07ef81b0e54a9486cfa25d769139f7">
      <documentation>A Digital Twin makes it possible to bring together and combine different types of data into a holistic view of a system, process, or entity. This combination helps to gain deeper insights, make better decisions, and generate value in various domains. This is an important instrument for data-driven work. With simulation, AI can also be used for 'opportunity finding'. The opportunity maps and what-can-go-where maps indicate areas with potential for solutions in case of conflicting interests in that area!</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Verified Data Assurance" id="id-8bb135c50fcf41c9a2c6d8568a2e3a69">
      <documentation>A Digital Twin stands (or falls) with the accurate representation (according to agreements and rules) of reality. All data and information that feed the digital twin are tested against agreed quality requirements. Errors are not to be avoided and user expectations are set accordingly. Trust is also obtained through formal agreements and frameworks. For example, the user must identify themselves in the system (Identity &amp; Access Management), confidential data is exchanged (data spaces), logging is performed, and APIs are managed (via gateway functionality).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Policy Indicator Calculation Service" id="id-4de442bc547e4df5946ba0eb85a802a7">
      <documentation>Digital Twins can use computational models (e.g., heat stress, waterlogging, noise zones). These computational models can analyse data using techniques and algorithms. This makes patterns and trends visible. These computational analyses can be used to gain insight into behavior and make predictions about future situations. The outcome of Computational Models translates into indicators. Indicators are the link between the Digital Twin and Policy. Calculating is therefore an essential part of both policy and a Digital Twin.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Holistic Situational Awareness" id="id-4d6f93c4284b4f1c814d9e34bc893b7a">
      <documentation>A Digital Twin makes it possible to define different policy perspectives and thus gain a holistic view of a policy area or policy project. This combination helps to gain deeper insights, make better decisions, and generate value in various domains. This is an important instrument for integrating all layers into 1 situational picture.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Policy Audit &amp; Reproducibility" id="id-6e8adf90a829494c87abbf3d5ef1b466">
      <documentation>Every policy decision (at a specific time) that is made using a digital twin must be reproducible at a later time. So the state that the Digital Twin has at a certain moment must be recallable, including the value of the indicators on which the decision was made. The reproducibility of the circumstances in which a policy decision is made, by means of a Digital Twin, is very important:&#xD;
In a constitutional state, decisions are made based on a legal framework and linked indicators, and&#xD;
The Digital Twin is truly seen as a policy instrument and that it can be trusted and helps in efficiency.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Real-time Urban Response" id="id-5631f579568d4563a14ef252d666fa3b">
      <documentation>Some Digital Twins are capable of processing (measurement) data in real-time, monitoring (to see if policy also has the desired effect in the policy cycle), and optionally reacting to changes. This requires computational rules (algorithms) that can quickly analyse data and take action based on results. Measurements are stored, so that in the future they can be used to make a statement about a series from the past to possibly observe a trend in indicators.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Proactive Outcome Forecasting Service" id="id-f0d9033a49224952bcba39569cb00b25">
      <documentation>Digital twins make it possible to anticipate future events, trends, or behaviors based on current and historical data of the simulated object or system. Using advanced analyses, models, and algorithms, a digital twin can simulate potential outcomes and scenarios, allowing users to react proactively to possible changes or challenges.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Decision Recording" id="id-fd315761b9e34e829f174817fb1a19a0">
      <documentation>Decision support involves the careful weighing of effects and interests and subsequently recording a choice based on the insights provided by the digital twin.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="LDT Workflow Management Service" id="id-974a6d13111b4448a14cc2a98853adf5">
      <documentation>Orchestration ensures that the different components or services within the Digital Twin work together to perform a specific task or workflow.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Urban Trend &amp; Behavior Analytics Service" id="id-79867d4a6cf74c8ab043a3550255810c">
      <documentation>Analysing is the process of examining and interpreting the data in the digital twin. This includes applying different analysis techniques, models, and algorithms to gain insights into the behavior, performance, and trends within the Digital Twin. The purpose of analysing is to see if control has the desired effect and can be adjusted for more or less effects where needed.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Metadata delivery" id="id-4609be09c66f4b4283bc67d95b321d18">
      <documentation>Describing the meaning, origin, timeliness, and use of data and models so they can be correctly understood and applied.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Provide Insight and Transparency" id="id-b166b5f483bb4fb382ccb389c59d3e73">
      <documentation>Explainability provides insight into the meaning of results from the digital twin by clarifying outcomes, patterns, and assumptions understandably and within their context.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="System Availability and assurance" id="id-86afff284ca541e58815eef0062a2943">
      <documentation>Observability provides insight into whether the digital twin is functioning properly as a system by tracking whether data, models, and visualisations cooperate correctly and timely.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Intervention Recording" id="id-2b2a601002714214acc3ce484c93da2c">
      <documentation>Decision support involves the careful weighing of effects and interests and subsequently recording a choice based on the insights provided by the digital twin.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessService" name="Collaborative Knowledge Training" id="id-e4e13f9defb046ae896210c71aa54c75">
      <documentation>Enables distributed AI training where data remains local, preserving organizational privacy</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="MIM1 - Interlinking Data" id="id-1f3e223f3eda4f6ab3f18b126076a9f8">
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="https://mims.oascities.org/"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="MIM 8 - Local Digital Twin" id="id-685d391170a4444da7c0a1f0531ecd26">
      <documentation>Draft reqs for MIM8:&#xD;
C1: Share data&#xD;
R1: Data can be exchanged across silos/sectors&#xD;
R2: LDTs (also across sectors) can work together to inform a use case&#xD;
R3:&#xD;
&#xD;
C2: Share services&#xD;
R1: Services can be exchanged across silos/sectors&#xD;
R2: The LDT can be applied to other data ecosystems with minimal integration effort&#xD;
&#xD;
C3: Share components&#xD;
R1: Common components can serve multiple local digital twin instantiation&#xD;
R2: The LDT is able to integrate new components across any of the layers, possibly from other LDTs from different sectors&#xD;
R3: The components from Layers (2), 3, 4 and 5 can be applied to other data ecosystems from different silos/sectors</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="https://mims.oascities.org/"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="MIM0 - Accessing Data" id="id-56b0ec3c0a4640a1810f3dfd88648e39">
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="https://mims.oascities.org/"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="MIM 2 - Representing Data" id="id-a6528a8a53cc438088c85a7547983169">
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="https://mims.oascities.org/"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="MIM 6 - Securing Data" id="id-1606a232f1ef4430b68a4592c55188fb">
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="https://mims.oascities.org/"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="MIM 3 - Sharing Data" id="id-76bd773953f249049b2e91f12cc2a498">
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="https://mims.oascities.org/"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="MIM 5 - Interoperable AI" id="id-87eb21f08e47415d8bf7eae06cc3f3d7">
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="https://mims.oascities.org/"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="MIM 7 - Geospatial" id="id-b36b734b4c6d4f288b2367af6f3f746d">
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="https://mims.oascities.org/"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Contract" name="MIM 4 - Personal Data" id="id-dffdd0fe8f9b4594ae4b759766b1a232">
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="https://mims.oascities.org/"/>
    </element>
  </folder>
  <folder name="Application" id="id-148e05fee7324f458fd675367269288c" type="application">
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationComponent" name="&lt;Applicatie Component>" id="id-bed9de38b7ff4dda920d42e4a4147e5d">
      <documentation>An encapsulation of application functionality aligned to&#xD;
implementation structure, which is modular and replaceable. It&#xD;
encapsulates its behavior and data, exposes services, and&#xD;
makes them available through interfaces</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Application Component>"/>
      <property key="Documentation (en)"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationService" name="&lt;Applicatie dienst>" id="id-b6862db2579e4c5e9bd7a107d4f07765">
      <documentation>An explicitly defined exposed application behavior.</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Application Service>"/>
      <property key="Documentation (en)"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="&lt;Data Object>" id="id-563bacfe19484c2284d72f4d9236491b">
      <documentation>Data structured for automated processing. A “Data entity”.&#xD;
Represents e.g. database, database table, message etc</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationInterface" name="&lt;Standaard Interface>" id="id-f4f3dc7b2c42485b8ad9e8919de28033">
      <documentation>A point of access where application services are made&#xD;
available to a user, another application component, or a node</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Standard Interface>"/>
      <property key="Documentation (en)"/>
    </element>
  </folder>
  <folder name="Technology &amp; Physical" id="id-2a39e97199f24312a22893f9306b58c4" type="technology">
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Node" name="&lt;Node>" id="id-c229cb065f0b42019f20e0453f692282">
      <documentation>A computational or physical resource that hosts, manipulates,&#xD;
or interacts with other computational or physical resources.&#xD;
Active structure elements that perform technology behavior&#xD;
and execute, store, and process technology objects such as&#xD;
artifacts. For instance, nodes are used to model application&#xD;
platforms, defined by the TOGAF framework as: “a collection&#xD;
of technology components of hardware and software that&#xD;
provide the services used to support applications”</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Node" name="EDIC Infrastrcture" id="id-ab201b577cb64eb89542bf3eba5eb939"/>
  </folder>
  <folder name="Motivation" id="id-5492b1ad6a614592a862d87862adc96b" type="motivation">
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="&lt;Implicatie>" id="id-0d0db954cb49481ab84ba68c12b3be84">
      <documentation>A statement of need that must be met by the architecture - more specific a consequence following from a principle</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Implication>"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="&lt;Architectuurprincipe>" id="id-5353a5472cd64b63a24f079f2022aecf">
      <documentation>A qualitative statement of intent that should be met by the&#xD;
architecture</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Principle>"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="&lt;Doel>" id="id-cc9506d1bedc4bd6bb58a403f2269ba2">
      <documentation>A high-level statement of intent, direction, or desired end state&#xD;
for an organization and its stakeholders</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Goal>"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="&lt;Driver>" id="id-703da37124dd4aa8adb37b955c6ee860">
      <documentation>An external or internal condition that motivates an organization&#xD;
to define its goals and implement the changes necessary to&#xD;
achieve them. Defines the WHY a change is important</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Driver>"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="&lt;Standaard>" id="id-3e5e79bef17e4a99b71ac55fe1e645ea">
      <documentation>A statement of need that must be met by the architecture - more specific a standard that needs to be followed to adhere to the architecture</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Standard>"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="&lt;Requirement>" id="id-06d3d5dfed584eb6987f4755aea00971">
      <documentation>A statement of need that must be met by the architecture</documentation>
      <property key="Name (en)" value="&lt;Requirement>"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Value" name="&lt;Value>" id="id-4602c93f66534ba8be7c7a051d89117e">
      <documentation>The relative worth, utility, or importance of a core element or&#xD;
an outcome.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Outcome" name="&lt;Outcome>" id="id-db58a19b5396449fa7e9c6240ebd3e0c">
      <documentation>An end-result that has been achieved. High-level, businessoriented results produced by capabilities, tangible, possibly&#xD;
quantitative.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Outcome" name="Contribution to Digital Europe Programme’s goals" id="id-cd05543764064768aaabf734ad11b77f">
      <documentation>LDT CitiVERSE EDIC directly contributes to the Digital Europe Programme’s&#xD;
goals by pooling EU and national resources, supporting interoperability, enabling secure data sharing, and&#xD;
enhancing digital capabilities across Member States, all while building a secure, scalable digital ecosystem&#xD;
that benefits Europe’s digital economy and public services alike.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.1 Objectives and activities"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Outcome" name="Operational Model that is market-oriented" id="id-e597258407344a6bbdacf77f117cdf07">
      <documentation>The Operational Model established by LDT CitiVERSE EDIC is market-oriented and&#xD;
regularly adjusted through engagement with stakeholders, ensuring long-term relevance and alignment with&#xD;
industry standards, while the strategic development plan positions the EDIC as a central enabler of multicountry projects, collaborating with leaders across industries to secure sustainable growth.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.1 Objectives and activities"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Creation of Interoperable European Solutions" id="id-205aab590e934af1bbc2555d478feef3">
      <documentation>Definition: The Creation of Interoperable European Solutions Driver represents an external or internal condition that motivates the public organisation to define its goals and implement the changes necessary to create Digital Public Services. 

Source: ArchiMate

Source reference: https://pubs.opengroup.org/architecture/archimate3-doc/index.html

Interoperability Dimension: Structural IoP

Viewpoint: Enterprise Architecture Framework alignment guidelines viewpoint

Identifier: http://data.europa.eu/dr8/CreationOfInteroperableEuropeanSolutionsDriver

ABB name: eira:CreationOfInteroperableEuropeanSolutionsDriver

EIRA concept: eira:ArchitectureBuildingBlock

Last modification: 2024-01-28

Identifier: http://data.europa.eu/dr8/CreationOfInteroperableEuropeanSolutionsDriver

Interoperability Layer: N/A

</documentation>
      <property key="eira:PURI" value="http://data.europa.eu/dr8/CreationOfInteroperableEuropeanSolutionsDriver"/>
      <property key="dct:type" value="eira:CreationOfInteroperableEuropeanSolutionsDriver"/>
      <property key="dct:modified" value="2024-01-28"/>
      <property key="eira:synonym"/>
      <property key="skos:definition" value="The Creation of Interoperable European Solutions Driver represents an external or internal condition that motivates the public organisation to define its goals and implement the changes necessary to create Digital Public Services. "/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="ArchiMate"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="https://pubs.opengroup.org/architecture/archimate3-doc/index.html"/>
      <property key="skos:example"/>
      <property key="eira:iopSaliency"/>
      <property key="skos:note"/>
      <property key="eira:iopDimension" value="Structural IoP"/>
      <property key="eira:viewpoint" value="Enterprise Architecture Framework alignment guidelines viewpoint"/>
      <property key="dct:identifier" value="http://data.europa.eu/dr8/CreationOfInteroperableEuropeanSolutionsDriver"/>
      <property key="eira:concept" value="eira:ArchitectureBuildingBlock"/>
      <property key="eira:eifLayer" value="N/A"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Objective O1: Infrastructure Development" id="id-ff0a8c42af7f4989a045acb29c2e643b">
      <documentation>Objective O1: Infrastructure Development&#xD;
&#xD;
• A1.1: Design and implement the required digital infrastructure to support EDIC's activities and objectives sustainably.&#xD;
&#xD;
• A1.2: Integrate the European Local Digital Twin Toolbox into the infrastructure, ensuring easy implementation for cities to support LDT adoption</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.1 Objectives and activities"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Objective O2: Technical Roadmap Design" id="id-4116f9e288054be09e4936dbf6e8e607">
      <documentation>Objective O2: Technical Roadmap Design&#xD;
&#xD;
• A2.1: Develop a detailed technical roadmap outlining development phases, milestones, and&#xD;
deliverables for the next three years&#xD;
&#xD;
• A2.2: Integrate advanced technologies such as AI, Data Spaces, and IoT to enhance the&#xD;
functionality, scalability, and adaptability of the LDT framework</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.1 Objectives and activities"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Objective O3: Service Definition and Implementation" id="id-7a9f42bfa2164d97962a6b0909944d38">
      <documentation>Objective O3: Service Definition and Implementation&#xD;
&#xD;
• A3.1: Define specific services for cities, focusing on LDT definition, deployment, and management.&#xD;
• A3.2: Implement user-friendly services to ensure wide-scale adoption of LDTs across European&#xD;
cities</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.1 Objectives and activities"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Objective O4: Capacity Building" id="id-b5b71b24aa434b228e4c0bcc7eb003ee">
      <documentation>Objective O4: Capacity Building&#xD;
&#xD;
• A4.1: Organize training sessions, workshops, and seminars to build skills and capacity among city&#xD;
agents and stakeholders in the smart city domain.&#xD;
&#xD;
• A4.2: Develop educational resources and best practice guidelines to support ongoing learning and&#xD;
stakeholder development</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.1 Objectives and activities"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Objective O5: Operational Model Definition" id="id-d28ac0393de94f46a3009e15b03a836f">
      <documentation>Objective O5: Operational Model Definition&#xD;
&#xD;
• A5.1: Define an operational model synchronized with market needs and aligned with the existing&#xD;
ecosystem of stakeholders.&#xD;
&#xD;
• A5.2: Engage with stakeholders to refine the operational model based on industry standards and&#xD;
evolving market demands through regular market analysis</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.1 Objectives and activities"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Objective O6: Strategic Development" id="id-adb8ae9d04b34c74b8c5318341e398d6">
      <documentation>Objective O6: Strategic Development&#xD;
&#xD;
• A6.1: Create a strategic plan to position the EDIC as the central enabler for Europe-wide multicountry projects for EU cities.&#xD;
&#xD;
• A6.2: Foster collaborations with industry leaders, academic institutions, and governmental bodies&#xD;
to ensure the sustainability and growth of the EDIC.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.1 Objectives and activities"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Citizen-centric approach" id="id-3def0d78508343f491c2e21a9ee954a1"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Intellectual Property Management" id="id-877eba8307f9416187f994648d4cb223"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Multi-layer Governance" id="id-3a5ffade1f4b4e049444e968577c6898"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Public report on the LDT Toolbox detailed specifications requirements" id="id-0f82dbe3fe674b57b10be94756134e7f">
      <property key="dct:modified" value="20-3-2026"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="https://data.europa.eu/doi/10.2759/384198"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Harmonised Standards for the European AI Act" id="id-f534d764240448dcbe9338cdf00d97c1">
      <property key="dct:modified" value="20-3-2026"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="https://publications.jrc.ec.europa.eu/repository/handle/JRC139430"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Value" name="Solidarity and inclusion" id="id-b8daf21b3b834c52befcabacb0417b52"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Value" name="People at the Centre " id="id-6b0208b444804db6bef5ff4b2899902c"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Value" name="Sustainability" id="id-4f858186192948bd823e1108aa5af4a4"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Value" name="Safety and Security" id="id-c92072bf743746839662856489026193"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Value" name="Participation" id="id-a078208f527746248e4d327115cc51bc"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Value" name="Freedom of Choice" id="id-61ca1d779256402fa4c557de67fcb82c"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="1. Federate Technical Assets and Ensure Interoperability" id="id-e22ff3dbee21409cb07d8c4707024e10">
      <documentation>LDT CitiVERSE EDIC will develop a unified digital twin infrastructure to connect Local Digital Twins&#xD;
(LDTs) across Europe, ensuring seamless interoperability through standardized specifications. This&#xD;
federation of platforms enables cities and regions to share data and resources, advancing a secure,&#xD;
interconnected digital ecosystem that strengthens the supply chain by eliminating siloed solutions and&#xD;
promoting shared innovation, leveraging previous DEP projects (e.g., Smart Communities, Data Space,&#xD;
EU LDT toolbox).</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="2. Promote Reusability and Avoid Redundancy" id="id-85d669c478804ce0a8e9284dbb0ca634">
      <documentation>By designing reusable digital twin assets, such as software, data models, and AI algorithms, LDT&#xD;
CitiVERSE EDIC will prevent redundant development efforts, allowing cities to allocate resources more&#xD;
efficiently. This approach supports cost-effective urban development, fosters a collaborative&#xD;
environment, and reinforces the supply chain by pooling assets and resources across regions, reducing&#xD;
dependency on external vendors by deploying an EDIC catalogue for tools and solutions for LDT</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="3. Support the EU CitiVERSE Vision" id="id-051ceda7de37448391735f2fe905c1b3">
      <documentation>LDT CitiVERSE EDIC will contribute to the foundation of the EU CitiVERSE by connecting LDTs and&#xD;
facilitating data-sharing and AI-driven services through Multi-Country Projects (MCPs). This networked&#xD;
approach will enhance data fluidity and support the EU’s vision of a resilient, collaborative digital&#xD;
infrastructure, bolstering supply chain security by embedding digital technology within EU-led&#xD;
frameworks</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="4. Develop a 4-Helix Ecosystem" id="id-4ad919ababfd4f67947f8aae0bf62dfc">
      <documentation>The project will establish a 4-Helix ecosystem that integrates public entities, private companies,&#xD;
academia, and citizens in co-developing open-source digital twin solutions. This self-sustaining&#xD;
community will co-maintain solutions, drive innovation, and ensure a steady supply of EU-driven&#xD;
advancements, thus reducing reliance on external technologies and fostering a vibrant innovation&#xD;
ecosystem within Europe.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="5. Strengthen European Strategic Autonomy" id="id-acb57f1ac5454c578e311d577b057d8f">
      <documentation>Ensuring that digital twin solutions are built and governed according to European standards and values&#xD;
is a priority for LDT CitiVERSE EDIC. The project emphasizes the development of digital skills and&#xD;
knowledge within the region, safeguarding EU digital sovereignty. This autonomy reinforces the supply&#xD;
chain by building capacity within Europe to develop, deploy, and manage digital twin solutions&#xD;
independently.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="6. Ensure Sustainable Investment and Deployment" id="id-33b47ea5c4c44c638c3d2b72d9fc276d">
      <documentation>By pooling resources from member states, cities and regions, LDT CitiVERSE EDIC will create a&#xD;
sustainable approach to deploying digital twin solutions. This sustainable model supports strategic longterm investments that are essential for consistent, reliable digital services. It allows cities to make datadriven policy decisions on urban challenges, enhancing the resilience of the supply chain through stable,&#xD;
EU-led investment channels</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="7. Fill Market Gaps with Sovereign Digital Twin Solutions" id="id-cb5905b80b38497785af81e987cb6194">
      <documentation>LDT CitiVERSE EDIC addresses gaps in the market by developing sovereign digital twin solutions that&#xD;
can be readily adopted by companies across Europe. This initiative promotes a competitive, innovationrich environment, supporting skill-building and knowledge development within the EU, and providing&#xD;
diverse, EU-created digital solutions.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="8. Contribute to the Digital Decade Objectives" id="id-bc388b3af67c4e5290cbf3c3816d3985">
      <documentation>The project supports the EU’s Digital Decade objectives by engaging ICT specialists, facilitating digital&#xD;
transformation in local businesses, and deploying technologies like AI, edge computing, and quantum&#xD;
computing. These efforts enhance the EU’s digital landscape, creating a supply chain that is both robust&#xD;
and aligned with the latest technological advancements.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="9. Enhance Data-Driven Decision-Making on Local Priorities" id="id-acb71c48e5dd42f791f5fafd81150c2c">
      <documentation>By enriching data capabilities, LDT CitiVERSE EDIC supports cities in making data-informed decisions&#xD;
around key local themes. This contribution enhances the supply chain by providing precise, targeted&#xD;
data insights, enabling local governments to respond effectively to evolving needs.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="10. Implement Robust Governance at Data and Algorithmic Levels" id="id-6915afd128954938acdfd35b73263c0d">
      <documentation>A governance structure for data and algorithms ensures transparent, secure management of digital twin&#xD;
resources. This framework increases accountability and oversight, reinforcing the digital supply chain by&#xD;
safeguarding data integrity and ensuring trustworthy, reliable solutions.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="11. Increase Trust Between Cities and Solution Providers" id="id-eb5f1ff4cef342dca31b70e782a37dd0">
      <documentation>By fostering trust between cities and technology providers, LDT CitiVERSE EDIC promotes the adoption&#xD;
of secure and reliable solutions. This relationship enhances the supply chain by facilitating consistent&#xD;
demand for quality, EU-based digital solutions, ensuring mutual benefit and security.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="12. Focus on Knowledge Building and Academic Engagement" id="id-b7a2d924274a4d1988d5c37aefed08ae">
      <documentation>Through academic initiatives, LDT CitiVERSE EDIC will build a strong foundation of knowledge and&#xD;
skills, ensuring that the EU has a steady pipeline of talent proficient in digital twin technologies. This&#xD;
emphasis on academia supports a sustainable, skilled supply chain within the EU.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="13. Move Beyond Research with EDIC-Driven Deployment" id="id-fcdad71c197d4de7a3b7eb293b328b2e">
      <documentation>With EDIC as the implementation backbone, LDT CitiVERSE EDIC transitions from research to realworld deployment, supporting applied digital technologies and reinforcing the digital supply chain by&#xD;
transforming research outcomes into tangible, sustainable solutions for European cities.</documentation>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="PROPOSAL_101225793-LDT CitiVERSE EDIC-DIGITAL-2024-BESTUSE-07-2.pdf"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="1.3 Digital technology supply chain"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Principle" name="European Library of Architecture Principles" id="id-b3fa95bd1cfd49578ca6d39c501c894a">
      <documentation>Definition: European Library of Architecture Principles (ELAP) ABB is a set of principles that aim to support interoperability and standardization in eGoverment across the EU.

Source: ELAP

Source reference: https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/collection/common-assessment-method-standards-and-specifications-camss/solution/elap

Additional information: The European Library of Architecture Principles (ELAP) ABB is a set of principles intended to direct government organizations in initiating changes and implementing IT projects. Particularly when designing new or modified services, it is necessary to make visible how the principles are implemented and which considerations are made in this regard. The apply-or-explain principle applies here, whereby deviations are permitted provided that they are substantiated and recorded with good arguments so that they can be revisited at a later stage. This prevents important matters from being overlooked.

Example: The following implementation is an example of how this specific Architecture Building Block (ABB) can be instantiated as a Solution Building Block (SBB): ELAP transparency principle in the EIF context refers to: Enabling visibility inside the administrative environment of a public administration. This is about allowing other public administrations, citizens, and businesses to view and understand administrative rules, processes, 11 data, services, and decision-making. Ensuring availability of interfaces with internal information systems. Public administrations operate a large number of what are often heterogeneous and disparate information systems in support of their internal processes. Interoperability depends on ensuring the availability of interfaces to these systems and the data they handle. In turn, interoperability facilitates reuse of systems and data, and enables these to be integrated into larger systems. Securing the right to the protection of personal data, by respecting the applicable legal framework for the large volumes of personal data of citizens, held and managed by Public administrations. https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/collection/common-assessment-method-standards-and-specifications-camss/solution/elap/distribution/elap-catalogue-v100xlsx

Interoperability Dimension: Governance IoP

LOST view: EIRA Ontology view

Interoperability Saliency: The European Library of Architecture Principles (ELAP) ABB is salient for governance interoperability due to it establishes the principles and framework to ensure interoperability at the European level. Also, the European Library of Architecture Principles ABB is salient for organizational interoperability due to it establishes requirements and business processes to enable interoperability between public services.

Identifier: http://data.europa.eu/dr8/EuropeanLibraryOfArchitecturePrinciplesPrinciple

ABB name: eira:EuropeanLibraryOfArchitecturePrinciplesPrinciple

EIRA concept: eira:ArchitectureBuildingBlock

Last modification: 2024-01-28

Identifier: http://data.europa.eu/dr8/EuropeanLibraryOfArchitecturePrinciplesPrinciple

Interoperability Layer: N/A

</documentation>
      <property key="eira:PURI" value="http://data.europa.eu/dr8/EuropeanLibraryOfArchitecturePrinciplesPrinciple"/>
      <property key="dct:type" value="eira:EuropeanLibraryOfArchitecturePrinciplesPrinciple"/>
      <property key="dct:modified" value="2024-01-28"/>
      <property key="eira:synonym"/>
      <property key="skos:definition" value="European Library of Architecture Principles (ELAP) ABB is a set of principles that aim to support interoperability and standardization in eGoverment across the EU."/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="ELAP"/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/collection/common-assessment-method-standards-and-specifications-camss/solution/elap"/>
      <property key="skos:example" value="The following implementation is an example of how this specific Architecture Building Block (ABB) can be instantiated as a Solution Building Block (SBB): ELAP transparency principle in the EIF context refers to: Enabling visibility inside the administrative environment of a public administration. This is about allowing other public administrations, citizens, and businesses to view and understand administrative rules, processes, 11 data, services, and decision-making. Ensuring availability of interfaces with internal information systems. Public administrations operate a large number of what are often heterogeneous and disparate information systems in support of their internal processes. Interoperability depends on ensuring the availability of interfaces to these systems and the data they handle. In turn, interoperability facilitates reuse of systems and data, and enables these to be integrated into larger systems. Securing the right to the protection of personal data, by respecting the applicable legal framework for the large volumes of personal data of citizens, held and managed by Public administrations. https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/collection/common-assessment-method-standards-and-specifications-camss/solution/elap/distribution/elap-catalogue-v100xlsx"/>
      <property key="eira:iopSaliency" value="The European Library of Architecture Principles (ELAP) ABB is salient for governance interoperability due to it establishes the principles and framework to ensure interoperability at the European level. Also, the European Library of Architecture Principles ABB is salient for organizational interoperability due to it establishes requirements and business processes to enable interoperability between public services."/>
      <property key="skos:note" value="The European Library of Architecture Principles (ELAP) ABB is a set of principles intended to direct government organizations in initiating changes and implementing IT projects. Particularly when designing new or modified services, it is necessary to make visible how the principles are implemented and which considerations are made in this regard. The apply-or-explain principle applies here, whereby deviations are permitted provided that they are substantiated and recorded with good arguments so that they can be revisited at a later stage. This prevents important matters from being overlooked."/>
      <property key="eira:concept" value="eira:ArchitectureBuildingBlock"/>
      <property key="eira:iopDimension" value="Governance IoP"/>
      <property key="eira:iopDimension" value="Behavioral IoP"/>
      <property key="eira:iopDimension" value="Structural IoP"/>
      <property key="eira:view" value="EIRA Ontology view"/>
      <property key="eira:view" value="Organisational view"/>
      <property key="eira:view" value="Semantic view"/>
      <property key="eira:view" value="Technical view - application"/>
      <property key="eira:view" value="Technical view - infrastructure"/>
      <property key="eira:view" value="EIRA Ontology viewpoint"/>
      <property key="dct:identifier" value="http://data.europa.eu/dr8/EuropeanLibraryOfArchitecturePrinciplesPrinciple"/>
      <property key="eira:eifLayer" value="N/A"/>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R35 - Swagger" id="id-316e2124458f4a628af9e618804c37cc">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must have their REST APIs documented using the OpenAPI specification with Swagger.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R33 - manuals" id="id-da74d7a385a542e9af33b480a304b5f5">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must have user and developer manuals.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R34 - C4Model" id="id-7e5f8533b24f4c55823d7beffdb4626f">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must have their architectures documented using C4Model diagrams specification.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R18 -  accessibility" id="id-0ea9d7d79cfd4290a37d310e9a23df9d">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should comply with accessibility guidelines for people with disabilities with a minimum of a WCAG 2.1 A level using WAI-Aria.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R13 - unified UX and UI" id="id-0f8f83e504ba4c68bddea093516903b2">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should have a unified UX and UI compliant with the EU LDT Toolbox visual identity guidelines.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R14 - preferences" id="id-10258a4d20c043789b056f4919d489c6">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should remember the user UI preferences and customizations.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R19 - GDPR-compliant" id="id-5f8b349aeb124f60862c173a28e6b996">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should support integration with GDPR-compliant user behaviour tracking and analysis tools.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R17 - responsive design" id="id-0f7b6ff3fd98407f96ec1fc8a6dc0d9e">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should use responsive design and must be compatible at least with their respective users’ preferred devices (Smartphones, tablets, laptops/desktops) and major AR/VR/MR devices.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R15 - quality criteria" id="id-9a1999504f3945318e7a892813b64284">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must comply with the quality criteria established on the “D03.02 EU LDT Toolbox Quality and Security Assurance Plan”.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R16 -  multilingual UI's" id="id-8fa29eaa5b094815bc37aeedbb96a4e6">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should have multilingual UIs, supporting at least all the official languages of the European Union.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R27 -  fault tolerance" id="id-ef4bd963c82d490ca17d161de640abe7">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should support configuration for auto-restarting instances of services when failing to improve fault tolerance.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R28 -  load balancing" id="id-c8b9f26b83954940bac8b70766d0784b">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should support configuration for load balancing configuration between instances of services when overloaded.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R32 - backup" id="id-37328c24dee744b79c0bc875f5184805">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must be able to create a backup copy of their data manually or automatically based on policy.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R25 -  monitoring" id="id-48c7707eb0914c788663ef9b4852db4a">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should support load balancing and monitoring using Istio.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R26 - logging" id="id-a8bfada6a59e4b54a05df3e162d612cd">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should provide quarriable logs of the actions performed by their users (identity, action, timestamp).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R30 - scalability" id="id-0cef86737e5e4cfdb24fccfa9acd31c8">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should support horizontal and vertical scalability.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R31 - auto-scaling" id="id-00b825cd81e74714aa64da5f1097a560">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must support configuration for auto-scaling depending on requests and resources.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R29 - resilience" id="id-2cb59f0e2ea5416492c59c6cba367757">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox HTTP connections should use resilience pipelines (Retry, Circuit Breaker, Timeout, Rate Limiter, and Fallback).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R23 - user support" id="id-63f35a30dd2a466596c480b66b8be573">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox of the EU LDT Toolbox should have a mechanism to reach user support.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R24 - health check endpoints" id="id-0c610eb7509247e881e54f675fc177bd">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should implement health check endpoints in a unified format and follow the recommended best practices.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R5 - cross-platform" id="id-79e3e6177ee94ab9b7d88347f74a8b4d">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must be cross-platform by providing provide web user interfaces.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R4 - standard data formats" id="id-f923e20d2ef34cdb9e624a4eb71d2ca4">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should provide well-structured and well-documented APIs using standard data formats to facilitate the integration of non-toolbox applications and services.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R3 - substitutable" id="id-410a3be4c9bc4df49a72bd9855651d2b">
      <documentation>Any tools of the EU LDT Toolbox should be substantiable for a different non-toolbox tool with the same functionality if they use the same standards.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R2 - interoperable" id="id-7a53a65d85eb46d08edec104abee5f63">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must be interoperable between themselves.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R1 - infrastructure-agnostic" id="id-8db6e6dd087d48d58f00a95199ba57b6">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must be problem and infrastructure-agnostic so that they can be used uniformly by different cities.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R20 - deployable" id="id-84ef7e46e06e4bfaa3db77326bbf3f38">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must be deployable on-premises and on cloud environments (Azure, GPC, AWS).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R21 - containerized" id="id-1b8a292d359644d7967034b1317c3ce4">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must be containerized using Docker.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R22 - distributed infrastructure" id="id-665566aa13ab482c82f0e3e2db0a14b3">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must be deployable in a distributed infrastructure using Kubernetes.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="OASC MIM's" id="id-80e37f45cafa4ac1ab465956618a5a70"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R8 - Identity Management" id="id-5606509f8e624ee3975f7e30ad21924a">
      <documentation>All tools of the EU LDT Toolbox should centralize their authentication and authorisation on the EU LDT Identity Management.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R7 - standard authentication, authorisation" id="id-abf49b0a9fdc48a99f17a9b46d444b86">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should use industry standard authentication and authorisation protocols (OAuth 2.0, SAML 2.0, WS-Federation, OpenID Connect, and JWT).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R12 - PII" id="id-63546c1cba5848f0b331727fe65130af">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should support cryptographic mechanisms to anonymize data for concealing Personally Identifiable Information (PII).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R11 - sandboxed" id="id-7d0397649aea460b96cda0a7b12a70b5">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox that enable to execute 3rd-party code should do so in a sandboxed environment to avoid creating remote code execution vulnerabilities.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R9 - EU Login" id="id-7688d4600117490ea9919cc64c51327f">
      <documentation>All sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should centralize their authentication and authorisation on the EU Login.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R10 -  secure communication protocols" id="id-ad0f7e199e524c79adad9e34d59af742">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox should communicate only using secure communication protocols (HTTPS and TLS/SSL).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Requirement" name="R6 - data protection guidelines" id="id-e5c1ae5665a340168458226451c739f9">
      <documentation>All tools and sites of the EU LDT Toolbox must comply with the data protection guidelines established on the “D07.01 EU LDT Methodology on Data Protection by Design and by Default”.</documentation>
    </element>
  </folder>
  <folder name="Implementation &amp; Migration" id="id-104af0de5c544412b35d455a8ef34161" type="implementation_migration">
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Plateau" name="&lt;LDT Implementations>" id="id-7c06575fac384cf8bdad9433630d0ca7">
      <documentation>A plateau represents a relatively stable state of the architecture that exists during a limited period of time.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Deliverable" name="&lt;LDT Solutions>" id="id-a42e55ae1e564b47bb1b0c73c7acc19d">
      <documentation>A deliverable represents a precisely defined result of a work package. Work packages produce deliverables.</documentation>
    </element>
  </folder>
  <folder name="Other" id="id-5a4959da49dd448caaf20a5409a66965" type="other">
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Grouping" name="eGovERA Business Agnostic Reference Architecture" id="id-c3b33eea6dfe43c6b3ecc9c0c0652738"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Grouping" name="Shared Legal Content" id="id-a1c2b1e78eb04b459678f6777be18097">
      <documentation>Definition: Shared Legal Content ABB is a Grouping setting legal (re)usable resources with convergence power, to public policy goals attainment, enabling to reuse and share legislations and cross-legal jurisdiction as key enablers for the creation of interoperable digital public services. 

Source: EUR-LEX 

Source reference: (https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A32021R0695&amp;qid=1646736486403)

Last modification: 2023-11-20

Identifier: http://data.europa.eu/dr8/SharedLegalContentGrouping

LOST view: Legal view

EIRA concept: eira:ArchitectureBuildingBlock

ABB name: eira:SharedLegalContentGrouping

Synonym: ABC

Example: The following implementation is an example on how this specific Architecture Building Block (ABB) can be instantiated as a Solution Building Block (SBB): The past years have seen an extraordinary proliferation of sharing economy platforms, and the largest platforms have fast become global enterprises with market capitalisations that exceed competitors with “traditional” business concepts. These developments call into question a number of regulatory matters and pose new questions for national and European-level regulators. (https://www.intereconomics.eu/contents/year/2017/number/1/article/regulating-the-european-sharing-economy-state-of-play-and-challenges.html).

Interoperability Saliency: The Shared Legal Content ABB is a key interoperability enabler (*) for governance, behavioural and structural interoperability because it supports to achieve of it with public policy goals convergence value by enabling i) sharing/provisioning/reusing/consumption of legislation on digital public services, ii) the exchange of data, information, and knowledge between digital public services, and iii) collaboration between digital public services. 

Additional information: The degree of achievement could range from an ideal perfect shared legal framework (i.e. no interoperability barriers from the legal perspective) to an imperfect or even null shared legal framework (i.e. some interoperability barriers from the legal perspective). The level of legal interoperability will constrain digital public services cross-legal jurisdictions. 

Interoperability Dimension: Structural IoP

Viewpoint: Highlevel viewpoint

Additional identifier: http://data.europa.eu/dr8/SharedLegalContentGrouping

EIF Layer: Legal

</documentation>
      <property key="eira:PURI" value="http://data.europa.eu/dr8/SharedLegalContentGrouping"/>
      <property key="dct:type" value="eira:SharedLegalContentGrouping"/>
      <property key="dct:modified" value="2024-04-29"/>
      <property key="eira:synonym" value="ABC"/>
      <property key="skos:definition" value="Shared Legal Content ABB is a Grouping setting legal (re)usable resources with convergence power, to public policy goals attainment, enabling to reuse and share legislations and cross-legal jurisdiction as key enablers for the creation of interoperable digital public services. "/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSource" value="EUR-LEX "/>
      <property key="eira:definitionSourceReference" value="(https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A32021R0695&amp;qid=1646736486403)"/>
      <property key="skos:example" value="The following implementation is an example on how this specific Architecture Building Block (ABB) can be instantiated as a Solution Building Block (SBB): The past years have seen an extraordinary proliferation of sharing economy platforms, and the largest platforms have fast become global enterprises with market capitalisations that exceed competitors with “traditional” business concepts. These developments call into question a number of regulatory matters and pose new questions for national and European-level regulators. (https://www.intereconomics.eu/contents/year/2017/number/1/article/regulating-the-european-sharing-economy-state-of-play-and-challenges.html)."/>
      <property key="eira:iopSaliency" value="The Shared Legal Content ABB is a key interoperability enabler (*) for governance, behavioural and structural interoperability because it supports to achieve of it with public policy goals convergence value by enabling i) sharing/provisioning/reusing/consumption of legislation on digital public services, ii) the exchange of data, information, and knowledge between digital public services, and iii) collaboration between digital public services. "/>
      <property key="skos:note" value="The degree of achievement could range from an ideal perfect shared legal framework (i.e. no interoperability barriers from the legal perspective) to an imperfect or even null shared legal framework (i.e. some interoperability barriers from the legal perspective). The level of legal interoperability will constrain digital public services cross-legal jurisdictions. "/>
      <property key="eira:concept" value="eira:ArchitectureBuildingBlock"/>
      <property key="eira:iopDimension" value="Structural IoP"/>
      <property key="eira:iopDimension" value="Behavioral IoP"/>
